The paper deals with motion planning for soccer playing robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian optimisation and machine learning techniques for trajectory optimisation and prior reuse suggests the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with obstacle avoidance and velocity profiling, which are related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of a simulator and testing on physical robots suggests the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) for visual perception and tracking.
